<p>I often want to type characters which aren‚Äôt on my keyboard, especially when writing HTML, characters such as: curly quotes, thin spaces, copyright symbols, em dashes, etc. In the past I would resort to using the HTML entities, e.g. <code>&amp;mdash;</code>, but as all my HTML files are encoded in UTF-8 it makes sense to type them directly, X11 makes that easy.</p>
<p>You simply assign a key on your keyboard to act as a ‚Äú<a href="http://www.x.org/releases/X11R7.7/doc/man/man5/Compose.5.xhtml">compose</a> key‚Äù, I use AltGr, but you can the Windows key, the menu key, caps lock, or any key you don't make use of. To set the AltGr key as your compose key type <code>setxkbmap -option compose:ralt</code> in your terminal, and/or put it in <code>~/.xinitrc</code> to make it permanent. That‚Äôs it! You can press your compose key and then type <code>12</code> to get ¬Ω, or <code>&lt;3</code> to get ‚ô•, or <code>!?</code> to get ‚ÄΩ. It‚Äôs as simple as that.</p>
<p>There are thousands of combinations preloaded, and most of them are very intuitive. You can see the full list in <code>/usr/share/X11/locale/en_US.UTF-8/Compose</code>. It‚Äôs also easy to add your own combinations, just place them in <code>~/.XCompose</code>, restart the application you want to use them in and you‚Äôre good to go.</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs my basic <code>~/.XCompose</code> which extends the defaults:</p>
<pre>
include "/usr/share/X11/locale/en_US.UTF-8/Compose"

# EMOTICONS
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;o> &lt;underscore> &lt;o>               : "‡≤†_‡≤†" # LOOK OF DISAPPROVAL
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;colon> &lt;D>                        : "üòÉ"   # :D
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;semicolon> &lt;parenright>           : "üòâ"   # ;)
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;colon> &lt;p>                        : "üòõ"   # :p
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;semicolon> &lt;p>                    : "üòú"   # ;p
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;colon> &lt;bar>                      : "üòê"   # :| 
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;colon> &lt;apostrophe> &lt;parenright>  : "üò¢"   # :'( 

# PUNCTUATION
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;bracketright> &lt;apostrophe> : "‚Äô"   U2019    # RIGHT SINGLE QUOTATION MARK
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;bracketleft> &lt;apostrophe>  : "‚Äò"   U2018    # LEFT SINGLE QUOTATION MARK
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;bracketright> &lt;quotedbl>   : "‚Äù"   U201d    # RIGHT DOUBLE QUOTATION MARK
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;bracketleft> &lt;quotedbl>    : "‚Äú"   U201c    # LEFT DOUBLE QUOTATION MARK
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;space> &lt;t>                 : "‚Äâ"   U2009    # THIN SPACE
&lt;Multi_key> &lt;space> &lt;m>                 : "‚ÄÉ"   U2003    # EM SPACE

